        "title_en": "Book 1 Ch.2: Some Objections",
        "summary_zh": "路易斯回应两种反对意见：一是道德律只是群体本能；二是道德律不过是社会习俗。他论证道德律既不等于本能，也不仅仅是社会约定，而是超越二者的客观实在。",
        "summary_en": "Lewis addresses two objections: that the moral law is merely herd instinct, and that it is merely social convention. He argues it is neither, but an objective reality transcending both.",
        "key_quotes": [
          "The most dangerous thing you can do is to take any one impulse of your own nature and set it up as the thing you ought to follow at all costs. 你能做的最危险的事情就是把自己天性中的某一种冲动当作不惜一切代价都要遵循的东西。"
