        "summary_zh": "虽然自然界启示上帝，但堕落的人类需要圣经作为'眼镜'来正确认识上帝。圣经的权威不来自教会的认可，而来自圣灵的内在见证。",
        "summary_en": "While nature reveals God, fallen humans need Scripture as 'spectacles' to know God rightly. Scripture's authority comes not from the church's endorsement but from the internal testimony of the Holy Spirit.",
        "key_quotes": [
          "Just as old or bleary-eyed men and those with weak vision, if you thrust before them a most beautiful volume, even if they recognize it to be some sort of writing, yet can scarcely construe two words, but with the aid of spectacles will begin to read distinctly; so Scripture, gathering up the otherwise confused knowledge of God in our minds, having dispersed our dullness, clearly shows us the true God. 正如老眼昏花的人，即使你把最精美的书摆在他们面前……但借助眼镜就能开始清楚地阅读；同样，圣经收集了我们心中原本混乱的对上帝的认识，驱散了我们的迟钝，清楚地向我们显明了真正的上帝。"
