    "summary_en": "Lewis explores the nature of four loves: Affection (Storge), Friendship (Philia), Eros, and Charity (Agape). He analyzes each love's beauty and danger—any natural love, if absolutized, becomes an idol and tyrant. Only divine love can purify and perfect the other three. The book combines literary beauty with theological depth.",
