        "summary_en": "Argues that all great civilizations acknowledge a common moral law—'the Tao.' Lewis extensively catalogs moral precepts from ancient Chinese, Indian, Greek, Jewish, Christian, Islamic, and other civilizations, proving universal human consensus on virtues like justice, honesty, mercy, and courage. This consistency demonstrates moral law's objectivity.",
        "key_quotes": [
