    "summary_en": "Davis's philosophical analysis of the epistemological value of religious experience. In religious philosophy, whether religious experience possesses evidential force remains a contentious issue. Davis employs analytical philosophical methods to deeply explore the epistemological status of mystical experiences, religious visions, answered prayers, and similar phenomena. She argues that under appropriate conditions, religious experience can provide reasonable evidential support for religious beliefs—while not decisive, sufficient to make religious belief rationally credible.",
